        ],
        [
          "Clustering",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "44 students on 2015/2\n40 students in 2016/1",
          "2 editions of a Discrete Mathematics course",
          "LMS logs",
          "Noe Specified",
          "Learning Path Graphs",
          "The LMS logs were converted into a Graph via the Plugin LPGraph.\n\nThe graph allows teachers to vizualize whether a learner followed the pre-specified learning path or if the learner differed.",
          "k-Means",
          "Expert Validation and Learning Gains from Activity 1 to Activity 2",
          "3",
          "The goal of M-Cluster is to create groups. This creation can follow multiple paradigms - heterogenous to homogenous groups.\n\n3 uneven clusters. With cluster 2 having 70% of the sample. ",
          "",
          "Authors create their own conceptual framework for group formation - TARGAVA.\n\nAuthors group the students using the k-means algorithm and attempt 3 distinct forms of distance metric: Euclidean, Manhattan or Cosine.\n\nAll suggested groups were validated by an expert professor to select the best course of action.\n\nLearners were allowed to form a team with members of the same cluster and, from activity 1 to  there was an overall improvement in performance of the students. \n",
          "- No interpretation of the clusters\n\nOnly explores k-means as an algorithm."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
  ],
