    {
      "id": "1924750c-f3ba-806c-8d5c-cb51a992b45d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Automated approaches to group formation are useful in distance learning situations. The approach of the authors uses LMS to understand learning paths and using these learning paths to make recommendations of teams for collaborative learning. Groups are done using k-means with attributes derived from different learning paths. REsults show that there is promise for improvement of student performance by up to 75%. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1924750c-f3ba-806c-8d5c-cb51a992b45d",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
